INVOKE.NAME: %$queue% != $null
INVOKE.COMMENT: support $queue input for backwards compatibility - prepend will return a new array, so no need to duplicate it

INVOKE.NAME: $default
INVOKE.COMMENT: take a copy of the $queues array, so that changes are not reflected back in the TN processing rule

LOOP.COMMENT: sanity check that all queues exist

INVOKE.NAME: $default
INVOKE.COMMENT: fetch real queue name, if configured on profile

EXIT.NAME: $null
EXIT.FAILURE-MESSAGE: Trading Networks Receiver's Queue does not exist for partner '%$condition.scope/$receiver/Corporate/CorporationName%' (ID = '%$condition.scope/$receiver/Corporate/PartnerID%')

EXIT.NAME: $null
EXIT.FAILURE-MESSAGE: Trading Networks queue '%$queues/name%' does not exist

SEQUENCE.NAME: $default
SEQUENCE.COMMENT: there are existing tasks for this queue, so instead of re-enqueuing we will restart existing failed tasks

SEQUENCE.NAME: %$tasks_for_queue/Status% == 3 or %$tasks_for_queue/Status% == 4
SEQUENCE.COMMENT: if existing task is FAILED or STOPPED, restart it rather than re-enqueue document

EXIT.COMMENT: only restart the first failed/stopped task
